    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 819.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 18, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 22d
                            ultimo, No. 561, which relates to the alleged enlistments on the
                            Kearsarge. It is not easy to discover the <pb facs="0110" n="100" xml:id="pg_100"/> points of difference between the consul’s
                            statements and the opposing ones to which Earl Russell refers. I can,
                            therefore, only renew the instruction authorizing you to investigate the
                            matter, and remove the consul, if he has offended, reporting the whole
                            case to me.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles F. Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
